  <description><![CDATA[<p>With its roots dating back to the turn of the 20th century, Hotel Villa Del Sogno is truly one of the best kept secrets of the <a data-udi="umb://document/7c2039e31003455f9c5af8c11e6f0e11" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7c2039e31003455f9c5af8c11e6f0e11}" title="Gardone Riviera">Gardone Riviera</a>. Perched high above the azure waters of the great lake, this Liberty-style property is home to antiques and bespoke works of art all connected to the history of the Villa itself. True to its Neoclassical inception, the great halls of the Villa Del Sogno are steeped in history with modern touches such as an onsite coffee house, wine bar and spa to emphasize the affluence of this spectacular hotel. </p>
<p>An elegant swimming pool is located in the heart of the gardens and the in house spa offers a plethora of unique and luxurious treatments which can be booked and purchased locally. An extensive buffet breakfast with hot and cold options is served each morning in the grand dining room or out on the terrace in warm weather and after a day exploring the lake from the ferry port just a 10 minute walk away, dinner can be taken out on the terrace for those on half board basis or those wishing to take a la carte at the Maximillian restaurant. </p>
<p>Please note that the centre of Gardone is approximately 2 kilometres away. A bus stop is located around 10 minutes from the hotel which can take you into the centre. </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
